        <b style = "text-decoration: underline;">
        Build a Simple Petition Page web application using Express MVC</b>
        <ul>
        <li>The web application requires only one HTML page 'Petition.html'.
        <li>The page displays a petition of your choice (~2 paragraphs and optional images).
        <ul><li>See https://www.change.org/petitionsLinks to an external site. for sample text. You can choose a random petition or you may create one on your own.</ul>
        <li>When the user scrolls down to the bottom of the petition page, they should see a form and a table.
        <li>The form should have two text fields (full name, city) and a checkbox which says that the "user agrees to sign the petition" (The usual click to agree text) followed by the submit button.
        <ul><li>You can add more fields to the form as you like.</ul>
        <li>The table should display the list of people who have signed so far (name & location)
        <ul><li>Optionally you may display more information</ul>
        <li>Please spend a bit of time for the front-end, so that it looks reasonably polished and aesthetically nice</ul>
        Things that you don't need to bother about<ul>
        <li>No need for login/authentication
        <li>No need for a database or an ORM like sequelize
        <ul><li>Don't even bother to use even an in-memory database
        <li>You can store the data in a simple Javascript array (yes, when the application restarts the data disappears and its ok)</ul></ul>
        <b style = "text-decoration: underline;">
        What to turn in</b>
            <ul>
        <li>Your code in a zip file
        <li>A screenshot of your application (PNG or JPEG)
        <li>(optional) Readme</ul>
        <b style = "text-decoration: underline;">
